net.proteusframework.ui.management.nav

Class NavigationLink

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.management.nav.NavigationLink
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource, Navigable, Component, ListCellRenderer, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellRenderer

    public class NavigationLink
extends ComponentImpl
implements TableCellRenderer, TreeCellRenderer, ListCellRenderer, Navigable
    A component that presents a clickable widget that opens a Link. The text value is displayed to the user. If no text value is set then the URI is displayed.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@venturetech.net)

      • getHTMLElement

        public Element getHTMLElement()
        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.

        Specified by:
        getHTMLElement in interface Component
        Returns:
        the element.
